# Architecture Rules

## Shell — always prefix commands with `rtk`
`rtk pnpm build` · `rtk git status` · `rtk rg foo` — 60-90% token savings.
Meta: `rtk gain` · `rtk discover`. Always Bash, never PowerShell.

## Monorepo packages
- `packages/shared` — IPC contracts + types. No React, no Node APIs.
- `packages/ui` — React component library. No app logic (no Zustand, no IPC).
- `packages/prompts` — AI prompt templates. Pure TypeScript, zero deps.
- `packages/core/ai/data/workers` — Backend only. Never import in renderer.
- `apps/desktop/src/renderer` — React UI. No direct Node.js access.

## IPC boundary
- Renderer talks to main ONLY through `window.api.*`
- Components NEVER call `window.api.*` directly — use service hooks
- Service hooks live in `apps/desktop/src/renderer/services/`
- IPC contract is the single source of truth: `packages/shared/src/ipc/contracts.ts`

## New capabilities checklist
1. Add to `packages/shared/src/ipc/contracts.ts`
2. Implement in `apps/desktop/src/main/ipc/router.ts`
3. Expose in `apps/desktop/src/preload/index.ts`
4. Create service hook in `apps/desktop/src/renderer/services/`

## Full documentation
- `docs/ARCHITECTURE.md` — process model, package roles, all data flows
- `docs/PATTERNS.md` — all 13 enforced coding patterns with examples
- `docs/DESIGN_SYSTEM.md` — color tokens, glass surfaces, motion system
- `docs/DEVELOPMENT.md` — setup, commands, debugging, CI
- `docs/RELEASE.md` — automated release pipeline and commit conventions

## Release
Releases auto-trigger on push to `main` via semantic-release.
`feat:` → minor, `fix:`/`perf:` → patch, `BREAKING CHANGE` → major.
Never manually tag or edit CHANGELOG.md/package.json version.
